Text.Value: A fresh Unholy Assassin. I remember the feeling - your ambition is to be commended.
No. For not killing enough of them. Father Bhaal cares not for a child that squanders his gifts.
I am most interested to see what will become of you, Child of Murder.
A fresh Unholy Assassin, and one of Bhaal's own blood.
I am Illasera the Quick. Child of Bhaal. Slayer of his idle children. Cut down before my time.
I best be leaving.
Yes... In Murder's embrace you shall want for naught.
I will do Bhaal's most unholy duty.
I remember when I dreamed of the same.
It is my destiny. I will be the last soul alive in this blighted world.
Anyone who squanders his gifts, in fact. Do not make that mistake, Unholy Assassin. He will be watching.
How do you know all this?
Leave a most grotesque path in your wake, Unholy Assassin. Lord Bhaal will be watching.
Do you feel the call as I do? The crawling in your blood?
Most wander this world like witless cattle - and you could become their butcher. Finish the ritual, Aspirant.
Is there no way for me to loosen Bhaal's hold?
No. My will is my own.
Who are you to commend me?
You are a chosen butcher now, little lamb. You shall lead many to his slaughter - whether you wish to or no.
You speak with arrogance - one that is familiar.
You remember... Kneeling afore a bucket. Scrubbing, scrubbing. It never works, does it?
It is a spot that will not scrub out.
Can't be that quick if someone cut you down.
In life - everyone thinks so. In death... You learn the folly of 'will'. I would know.
Walk in the footsteps of murder, Child of Bhaal. Our Father is impatient for the blood-gifts of your slaughter.
Haven't you felt it, Holy Child? Bhaal has a noose around your neck. You must trust him, and leap.
Is that why you're here? Punishment for killing Bhaal's offspring?
You are to be commended, though I expected nothing less from a Child of Murder.
Walk in blood, Unholy Assassin. Stalk your prey swift, but savour their kill.
The same arrogance has slain many of Bhaal's Chosen. Do not repeat our mistakes, Unholy Assassin.
Speaking of time - I've better things to do with mine. Goodbye.
Most wander this world like witless cattle - but you are the butcher. Finish the ritual, Bhaalspawn.
Unholy Assassin, your birth was a miracle. Bhaal conceived you from a place beyond mortality.
Your birth, your creation... Father tended to you with love... He made you perfection...
It's perfect. Finally I feel free.
We are his Justices. We preside over his most profane tribunal - forevermore.
I don't like it. I feel... tainted.

Synopsis: Dialogue with the ghost of Illasera, bound to eternal service to Bhaal in her afterlife. In "Baldur's Gate 2: Throne of Bhaal", Illasera was one of the Five, an evil group of Bhaalspawn led by Amelyssan.
